<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 16 at 3:46PM EDT  by NWS Cleveland</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northern Huron, Erie
and west central Lorain Counties through 430 PM EDT...
At 346 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Northern Milan, or over Norwalk, moving southeast at 35 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Norwalk, New London, Milan, Northern Milan, Wakeman, Oberlin,
Monroeville, Berlin Heights, Kipton and Rochester.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
